{"word":"βούθυτος","slug":"βούθυτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βούθυτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>θύω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>of</i> or <i>belonging to sacrifices</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>of oxen</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>on which oxen are offered, sacrificial</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}